@@ -206,6 +209,24 @@ ### Asset Exclusion
 
 Individual assets can be excluded from calculations via `excludedAssetIds`. Excluded assets are filtered out of `effectivePositions`.
 
+### Consolidated Issuer Exposure (FGC / Crédito Privado)
+
+The Bancários (FGC) and Crédito Privado tables under [RFBancariosCP.vue](../../src/resources/js/Features/Client/Allocation/Components/rf/RFBancariosCP.vue) intentionally **ignore** `AccountSelector`. Concentration limits in those instruments apply to the investor's CPF, not to a single broker — FGC caps at R$ 250k per institution per CPF (R$ 1M overall), and private credit issuer concentration is also tracked across all wallets.
+
+To support this, `useAllocationDashboard` exposes two parallel computeds that operate over every account regardless of selection:
+
+| Selection-scoped | Consolidated equivalent |
+|---|---|
+| `effectivePositions` | `allEffectivePositions` |
+| `rfPositions` | `consolidatedRfPositions` |
+| `totalEquity` | `consolidatedTotalEquity` |
+
+Both consolidated computeds still apply `strategyOverrides` and `excludedAssetIds` (advisor configuration is honored), but they skip the `selectedAccountIds` filter.
+
+`AllocationDashboard` passes both pairs into `RFAllocation`. `RFAllocation` routes the selection-scoped data to the maturity ladder, RF aporte summary, and approved-products section, and the consolidated pair to `RFBancariosCP` — which then feeds both `RFBancariosTable` (FGC) and `RFCreditoPrivadoTable`. The `% PL` column in those two tables is therefore calculated against `consolidatedTotalEquity`, so the percentages reflect the client's true concentration.
+
+A subtitle on each of the two tables makes the consolidation explicit so advisors don't mistake stale numbers for a broken filter.
+
