@@ -536,4 +557,5 @@ ## Sensitive Areas
 - The `AssetService` caches rankings and fixed income offers for 1 hour. Approved issuers are cached for 1 day. Stale data is possible within those windows.
 - Treasury strategy mapping relies on code prefix matching. New treasury instrument types would need manual addition to `TREASURY_STRATEGY_MAP`.
 - The equity allocation engine's full lot rounding and leftover redistribution are purely client-side computations — no backend validation exists for the generated orders.
+- The Bancários (FGC) and Crédito Privado tables in [RFBancariosCP.vue](../../src/resources/js/Features/Client/Allocation/Components/rf/RFBancariosCP.vue) deliberately ignore `AccountSelector` to surface CPF-level concentration. Anyone changing the RF data pipeline must keep `consolidatedRfPositions` / `consolidatedTotalEquity` flowing through that component, or the percentages will silently shift to a selection-scoped view and misrepresent regulatory exposure.
 - Frontend changes in this module should stay within `Features/Client/Allocation/` and follow Shadcn as the target UI standard.
